commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, UniCash starts populated with sample data.

However, once this data is cleared, there is no way to restore the
sample data apart from manually deleting the unicash.json storage
which would require the user to bypass the App and access its storage
files directly.

Let's fix this minor issue by allowing the user, and any possible
testers of the UniCash application to restore the UniCash to its
initial default state such that any data-modification actions or tests
can be conveniently reversed.

commitResults.messageBody: Add Reset Functionality to UniCash

Previously, each transaction would be appended to the bottom of the
transaction list panel, which would impede the user from getting
immediate response as to their input, as the TransactionListPanel does
not scroll automatically.

Rather than making the panel auto-scroll, let's reverse
the order of the list so that the user is always looking at the most
recent transaction.

Additionally, let's modify the CommandBox to span the whole Window
with a smaller font size so that it can accomodate a longer input
command.

In order to adhere to Demeter's principle, this method has been
added for the upcoming `UniCash#getSumOfExpensePerCategory`, which
uses the transactions' Amount for calculations.

Let's implement the `Transaction#getAmountAsDouble` method and add
unit tests to test this method.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add updateExpenseSummary to Model and ModelManager
commitResults.messageBody:
In order to interact with the UI, ModelManager needs an attribute
to allow the UI to directly get the required data for plotting the
pie chart.

Let's add an `expenseSummary` HashMap<String, Double> for this. The
`expenseSummary` hashmap maps the expense Category to a value, which
represents the total expense for that category. The
updateExpenseSummary method will update the `expenseSummary` hashmap
when there are changes in the transactions. This warrants the need
for other methods that directly modify the transactions in UniCash
to also be updated to call this method when they make changes in the
transactions. Unit tests that test the added methods have also been
added.

Note 1: `UniCash#getSumOfExpensePerCategory` is the method that
calculates the expenses per category, while
`Model#updateExpenseSummary` simply uses the result of the
calculations to update `expenseSummary`.
Note 2: The `AddTransactionCommandTest` has been modified because
the ModelStub class has to implement the
`Model#updateExpenseSummary` prototype.

commitResults.messageBody:
`SummaryWindow` is currently plotting fictional (hardcoded) pie
chart data. Thus, it is not plotting the true data in UniCash.

Let's link the `expenseSummary` attribute of UniCash to
`SummaryWindow`. Since `MainWindow` is the UiPart that links `Logic`
and `SummaryWindow` together, we first modify the `SummaryWindow`
constructor to take in a `HashMap<String, Double> expenseSummary`.
Then, within `MainWindow`, when constructing `SummaryWindow`, we
pass in the `expenseSummary` hash map as an input to link
`MainWindow` and `SummaryWindow`. Next, we link `expenseSummary` to
`MainWindow` by creating the `getExpenseSummary` method in `Logic`
and `LogicManager`. Lastly, we edit `SummaryWindow#setPieChart` to
modify the pie chart's data using `expenseSummary`, instead of the
fictional (hardcoded) data.

Note 1: `MainWindow#handleSummary` now calls
`SummaryWindow#setPieChart` so that when the user executes the
"summary" command, the pie chart will be updated accordingly.
Note 2: The current implementation uses for-loops extensively. This
will later be modified to use Java streams instead.

commitResults.messageTitle: Modify `MainWindow` to update pie chart whenever a new command is run
Fix scrambled pie chart label bug
commitResults.messageBody:
When the user closes the pie chart and opens it again using the
"summary" command, the labels of the pie chart are scrambled up.

Let's fix this bug by calling the `VBox#layout` method after adding
the pie chart data.

Note: This solution was suggested here:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/49843498/java9-bug-in-javafx-piechart-labels

commitResults.messageTitle: Modify `SummaryWindow.fxml` to remove animations and disable resize
commitResults.messageBody:
The pie chart's animations plays every time the user runs a command,
which might be distracting. Also, resizing the summary window may
cause the plot and words to be displayed strangely.

Let's disable window-resizing and animations to fix these issues.

`SummaryWindow#setPieChart` now does not take in any parameters. It
is able to directly access `UniCash#expenseSummary`. It may be
better to restrict `SummaryWindow`'s access to `expenseSummary`.

Let's modify `SummaryWindow#setPieChart` to take in `expenseSummary`
as a parameter instead. `MainWindow`'s initialization of
`SummaryWindow` also has to be updated due to `SummaryWindow`'s
constructor changing.

Modify test cases due to changes to Category constructor
commitResults.messageBody:
There are several test cases for LogicManager, ModelManager, and UniCash
that are failing due to the changes to the Category(String) constructor.
In particular, categories have been modified by Rubesh to be set to
lowercase. This causes the expected behavior of test cases that rely on
this constructor to change.

Let's modify the test cases to reflect this change in expected behavior.
We simply modify the expected categories to have all lowercase chars.
